cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GR. 

The paper deals with algorithms for triangulating a simple polygon, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm also uses space-efficient techniques, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also mentions shortest-path maps and partitioning the polygon, which are related to graph algorithms and computational topology, respectively, so cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GR (Computer Graphics) are also possible sub-categories.
